What you do manually (10 min, one-time)
Create a free Cloudflare account at cloudflare.com (if you don't have one)
Install Wrangler (Cloudflare's CLI): npm install -g wrangler
Authenticate: npx wrangler login — opens browser, click "Allow"
Add groomd.app to Cloudflare (for the api.groomd.app custom domain):
In Cloudflare dashboard: "Add a site" → enter groomd.app → select Free plan
Cloudflare will give you two nameservers (e.g. ada.ns.cloudflare.com, ben.ns.cloudflare.com)
Go to your domain registrar (wherever you bought groomd.app) and change the nameservers to the Cloudflare ones
Important: Cloudflare will import your existing DNS records. Verify that the GitHub Pages records are preserved (CNAME or A records pointing to GitHub). This keeps groomd.app working as-is.
DNS propagation takes 5 min to a few hours
Shortcut if you want to skip DNS for now: We can use *.workers.dev URL instead of api.groomd.app. This means zero DNS changes — everything works immediately. You can add the custom domain later. The only difference is the URL in the network tab says groomd-api.YOUR_ACCOUNT.workers.dev instead of api.groomd.app.

What Claude Code does (hand it off after step 3 above)
Once wrangler login is done, Claude Code can handle everything else:

Write cloudflare-worker/worker.js and cloudflare-worker/wrangler.toml
Run npx wrangler deploy to push the worker live
Run npx wrangler domains add api.groomd.app to attach the custom domain (if DNS is set up)
Test with curl to verify the proxy works
Write vail-lifts.html with the ski-sign design
Update index.html footer link
Commit and push to deploy to GitHub Pages
Can Claude cowork handle DNS? Not the registrar nameserver change (that's a web UI at your registrar). But everything else — Cloudflare Worker creation, deployment, custom domain attachment, and all the code — yes, fully automatable via wrangler CLI. The manual part is truly just "change nameservers" and "click Allow on the wrangler login page."